      <p>Let <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf50.jpg"/></inline-formula> be the matrix corresponding to the parameter <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf51.jpg"/></inline-formula> of the variance matrix Var (<inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf52.jpg"/></inline-formula> in Equation 9. Define the test statistic for testing the interaction between the two genomic regions <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf53.jpg"/></inline-formula> and <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf54.jpg"/></inline-formula> as<disp-formula id="DE10"><graphic xlink:href="989equ13.jpg" position="float"/></disp-formula>Then, under the null hypothesis <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf55.jpg"/></inline-formula>, <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf56.jpg"/></inline-formula> is asymptotically distributed as a central <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf57.jpg"/></inline-formula> distribution if <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="989inf58.jpg"/></inline-formula> components are taken in the expansion Equation 6.</p>
